OL,3,CHead of Caldey Abbey apologises for
OL,4,C'great suffering' of abused children
OL,6,FThe head of an abbey on a remote Welsh
OL,7,Fisland has apologised for the "great
OL,8,Fsuffering" endured by children who
OL,9,Fwere abused by a late monk, and the
OL,10,F"culture of secrecy and cover-up" that
OL,11,Fkept it hidden, after an independent
OL,12,Freview.
OL,14,FFather Jan Rossey, who last year
OL,15,Fbecame the Abbot of Caldey Abbey, off
OL,16,Fthe the coast of Pembrokeshire and
OL,17,Fhome to Cistercian Order monks,
OL,18,Fcommissioned a review into alleged
OL,19,Fhistorical child sexual abuse by monks.
